Notable

What and why of Noteable

Noteable is a service which provides hosted access to Jupyter notebooks - it is maintained by EDINA and the university’s Information Services. Access is provided free to all UoE staff and students.

Noteable is equivalent to running a Jupyter notebook on your local machine, except that all of the configuration and systems administration has been taken care of (e.g. all of the necessary Python packages are already installed). Additionally, as it is entirely web based you will be able to connect from any device with a web browser.

For some useful introductory materials please see the documentation here

Logging in

As a UoE student you should already have access to Noteable and can login using your university creditials via ease. You can connect to the service via this link.

Once logged in make sure to start a “Language and Machine Learning” instance to have access to various libraries, and you should be ready to go.

Importing code to Notable

The code for scraping the data from the Financial Ombudsman website has been provided on GitHub here:

https://github.com/wilsonamy/SWDS_simply_business

To copy this into your notable instance, click +git repo, enter the url of the GitHub repository and click clone.
